## Bageasy Login and Checkout Automation Script (with Selenium)##	

This script automates the login and checkout process for a specific product on the Bageasy website ([https://bageasy.in/](https://bageasy.in/)). 

Requirements:

 Python 3.x
 Selenium WebDriver
 Webdriver for your desired browser (Firefox in this case)

Installation:

1. Install Python from [https://www.python.org/downloads/](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
2. Install Selenium WebDriver using pip: `pip install selenium`
3. Download the appropriate WebDriver for your browser from [https://chromedriver.chromium.org/](https://chromedriver.chromium.org/) or [https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases](https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases)
4. Place the WebDriver executable in your system path or set the path using `Service` class.

Instructions:

1. Create a new file named `credentials.py` and add the following lines, replacing the placeholders with your actual Bageasy login credentials:

```python
credentials.username = "your_username@example.com"
credentials.password = "your_password"
```

2. Run the script `bageasy_automate.py` (replace with your actual filename).

Functionality:

 Opens Bageasy website in Firefox browser.
 Clicks on the Login button.
 Fetches username and password from `credentials.py` and enters them in the login form.
 Clicks on the Login button again.
 Navigates to a specific product page (modify the XPATH selector if needed).
 Clicks on the "Add to Cart" button for the product.
 Clicks on the "Cart" icon.
 Clicks on the "Checkout" button.
 Waits for 5 seconds (you can modify this time).


